1
00:00:56,182 --> 00:00:58,350
EPISODE 10

2
00:01:28,005 --> 00:01:29,173
RECIPIENT: HAN SEO-YUL

3
00:01:31,050 --> 00:01:32,051
[camera shutter clicks]

4
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:51,946
STAFF JU HYUN-SU

5
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:25,688
[elevator bell dings]

6
00:02:29,608 --> 00:02:30,734
[elevator bell dings]

7
00:02:59,221 --> 00:03:01,473
Geez, this careless punk.

8
00:03:02,057 --> 00:03:03,851
I told him not to get stuff
delivered here.

9
00:03:05,686 --> 00:03:06,687
[door lock beeps]

10
00:03:35,674 --> 00:03:38,677
Seol-ah, what are you doing here?

11
00:03:39,762 --> 00:03:41,002
I could ask you the same thing.

12
00:03:42,598 --> 00:03:44,350
The man that you just saw…

13
00:03:45,601 --> 00:03:46,936
Is Ju Hyun-su.

14
00:03:47,728 --> 00:03:49,021
He killed my sister.

15
00:03:52,191 --> 00:03:53,692
Why were you chasing him too?

16
00:03:53,776 --> 00:03:55,361
I wasn't chasing after him.

17
00:03:56,028 --> 00:03:58,530
I came to find Chair Kim's
property under a pseudonym.

18
00:04:01,075 --> 00:04:02,868
So, he was in Chair Kim's building?

19
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:08,999
Could there be some kind of
connection between the two?

20
00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:11,627
For now, it's just speculation.

21
00:04:12,544 --> 00:04:14,004
Let's go somewhere else.

22
00:04:14,088 --> 00:04:15,965
- We shouldn't be talking about this...
- But I…

23
00:04:16,966 --> 00:04:18,509
I have nothing more to say.

24
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:21,011
Everything I know ends here.

25
00:04:27,393 --> 00:04:29,103
Are you feeling okay?

26
00:04:33,399 --> 00:04:35,150
You've been
taking care of yourself, right?

27
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:41,490
Listen, Woo-seok.
You stay safe, all right?

28
00:04:53,961 --> 00:04:54,962
[sighs]

29
00:04:58,132 --> 00:04:59,133
[sighs]

30
00:05:09,601 --> 00:05:11,770
<i>The man that you just saw is Ju Hyun-su.</i>

31
00:05:11,854 --> 00:05:13,355
<i>He killed my sister.</i>

32
00:05:14,023 --> 00:05:16,108
Ju Hyun-su in Chair Kim's building?

33
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:20,061
Could there be some kind of
connection between the two?

34
00:05:38,672 --> 00:05:40,257
[Woo-hee] <i>I didn't lie like the others.</i>

35
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,384
Ugh, quit worrying.

36
00:05:42,468 --> 00:05:44,863
I told them straight up that
I was going on a trip with my boyfriend.

37
00:05:44,887 --> 00:05:46,156
So, you should trust me too, brother.

38
00:05:46,180 --> 00:05:48,265
Wow, when did you grow up so much?

39
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:50,142
You always treat me like a child.

40
00:05:50,726 --> 00:05:52,895
At this rate, I'll get married before you.

41
00:05:52,978 --> 00:05:56,356
Ms. Cha Woo-hee, easy, all right?

42
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:57,733
Getting married, already?

43
00:05:57,816 --> 00:05:59,777
Over there. Just drop me off there.

44
00:06:04,615 --> 00:06:06,116
Call me when you get to Busan.

45
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,451
Hey, you can eat that.

46
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:08,577
Be careful, okay?

47
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:09,745
Okay.

48
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:17,628
[chuckles]

49
00:06:23,926 --> 00:06:26,220
[phone buzzing]

50
00:06:28,305 --> 00:06:29,598
Hey, Woo-hee.

51
00:06:29,681 --> 00:06:31,225
<i>Mr. Cha Woo-seok, right?</i>

52
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:35,020
<i>Hello. I'm Woo-hee's boyfriend.</i>

53
00:06:36,855 --> 00:06:38,857
Ms. Cha, who was seated
in the passenger seat,

54
00:06:38,941 --> 00:06:40,067
was not wearing a seat belt.

55
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:41,211
PHOTOS FOR COURT SUBMISSION

56
00:06:41,235 --> 00:06:43,338
A sleep-inducing agent was
detected in her bloodstream.

57
00:06:43,362 --> 00:06:44,613
At the recommendation…

58
00:06:44,696 --> 00:06:45,781
PROSECUTION

59
00:06:45,864 --> 00:06:47,533
…of the defendant, Ju Hyun-su,

60
00:06:47,616 --> 00:06:50,202
she had taken out
a $210,000 life insurance policy.

61
00:06:50,285 --> 00:06:51,679
POLICYHOLDER: CHA WOO-HEE
BENEFICIARY: JU HYUN-SU

62
00:06:51,703 --> 00:06:53,890
There are circumstances that
raise suspicion about the accident…

63
00:06:53,914 --> 00:06:55,207
JUDGE

64
00:06:55,290 --> 00:07:00,254
…but there's no objective evidence
to conclude that it was intentional.

65
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,715
<i>Only the charge of
causing the victim's death</i>

66
00:07:03,799 --> 00:07:05,425
<i>through negligence is sustained.</i>

67
00:07:05,509 --> 00:07:10,514
<i>The defendant, Ju Hyun-su,
is hereby sentenced to one year in prison.</i>

68
00:07:10,597 --> 00:07:12,641
[gavel bangs]

69
00:07:15,894 --> 00:07:17,020
[breathes shakily]

70
00:07:30,868 --> 00:07:34,079
<i>That's evidence of having
transported some kind of artwork.</i>

71
00:07:42,045 --> 00:07:43,714
<i>But why Ju Hyun-su?</i>

72
00:08:08,822 --> 00:08:12,242
You said that you saw Han Seol-ah
coming down from the rooftop

73
00:08:12,326 --> 00:08:14,411
on the day Kim Yun-ji died.

74
00:08:14,953 --> 00:08:19,374
But yet you're the only one
without an alibi for the time of her fall.

75
00:08:20,751 --> 00:08:23,671
Aren't you trying to frame Han Seol-ah
when you're the one who killed her?

76
00:08:23,754 --> 00:08:26,298
You even made the tip-off call
with your voice altered.

77
00:08:26,381 --> 00:08:27,674
No! No!

78
00:08:27,758 --> 00:08:29,384
I did not kill anyone.

79
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:31,345
Well, listen,

80
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:35,557
it looks like you don't even understand
what charges you're sitting here for.

81
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:38,977
I only followed Han Seol-ah
to see what she was up to.

82
00:08:51,573 --> 00:08:53,033
- [door closes]
- [car door closes]

83
00:09:00,082 --> 00:09:01,583
[sighs]

84
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:04,086
I thought it was suspicious
when I saw them sneaking out.

85
00:09:04,169 --> 00:09:08,465
I was determined to find out that time…
[sighs] …but I lost them again.

86
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:11,301
"Again"?

87
00:09:17,849 --> 00:09:19,601
That's right. [Breathes deeply]

88
00:09:19,685 --> 00:09:21,478
The day Ms. Kim died,

89
00:09:23,355 --> 00:09:25,732
I was the one who took that video.

90
00:09:29,987 --> 00:09:31,738
[Seol-ah] What are you trying to say?

91
00:09:32,364 --> 00:09:33,657
[Ms. Kim] I wonder…

92
00:09:34,283 --> 00:09:37,995
If your secret came out
for the whole world to see,

93
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:40,455
would you still be this graceful?

94
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:42,040
[scoffs]

95
00:09:46,545 --> 00:09:49,881
And why did you keep following
Han Seol-ah around?

96
00:09:49,965 --> 00:09:51,258
You're asking me why?

97
00:09:51,842 --> 00:09:53,969
Because the police
couldn't even catch her!

98
00:09:54,052 --> 00:09:55,321
Because you're not doing your jobs.

99
00:09:55,345 --> 00:09:58,598
Even now, you're holding me here
when I've done nothing wrong!

100
00:09:58,682 --> 00:09:59,766
Why are…

101
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:01,393
Why are you people doing this to me?

102
00:10:01,476 --> 00:10:04,021
What did I even do wrong?
[breathing shakily]

103
00:10:05,731 --> 00:10:07,357
I didn't kill anyone.

104
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,738
[cries]

105
00:10:18,201 --> 00:10:19,536
[sighs]

106
00:10:22,414 --> 00:10:25,876
So, you're saying you didn't
supply champagne that day?

107
00:10:27,044 --> 00:10:28,378
Uh, no.

108
00:10:28,462 --> 00:10:32,507
It was a VIP event, so Chair Kim
said she'd handle it herself.

109
00:10:32,591 --> 00:10:34,176
Chair Kim from the auction house?

110
00:10:34,259 --> 00:10:35,385
Yeah.

111
00:10:35,469 --> 00:10:38,805
The champagne Mr. Paek drank
and collapsed from, it wasn't ours.

112
00:10:40,557 --> 00:10:42,142
Then why did you attend the event?

113
00:10:44,353 --> 00:10:48,231
I didn't sneak in. I got in the proper way
with Seol-ah's invitation, you know.

114
00:10:48,315 --> 00:10:50,817
No, why you went.

115
00:10:50,901 --> 00:10:53,111
What was your purpose
in attending the event?

116
00:10:53,779 --> 00:10:54,821
[sighs]

117
00:10:56,448 --> 00:10:58,367
I thought, if I met a decent guy,

118
00:10:59,576 --> 00:11:02,245
[sighs] I might try to get
something going with him.

119
00:11:04,206 --> 00:11:06,583
Honestly, I love parties.

120
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:09,795
In Korea, there aren't many
opportunities to wear dresses.

121
00:11:10,420 --> 00:11:13,882
But you weren't even on
the guest list the day Kim Yun-ji died.

122
00:11:14,466 --> 00:11:15,967
Did you go just to wear a dress?

123
00:11:16,051 --> 00:11:18,970
[sighs] I really didn't do anything crazy.

124
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,181
You did something.

125
00:11:21,264 --> 00:11:22,808
No, I did not.

126
00:11:22,891 --> 00:11:25,727
I just thought that girl, Kim Yun-ji,
was so strange…

127
00:11:26,311 --> 00:11:28,146
Ms. Han only drinks decaf coffee, right?

128
00:11:29,272 --> 00:11:30,440
Okay.

129
00:11:33,735 --> 00:11:34,778
Here's your coffee.

130
00:11:35,445 --> 00:11:36,530
Thank you.

131
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:38,407
DECAF

132
00:11:49,668 --> 00:11:50,836
Here you go.

133
00:11:51,586 --> 00:11:52,879
How are things?

134
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:01,930
[gasps]

135
00:12:04,599 --> 00:12:05,684
What's wrong with you?

136
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:06,768
What's your deal?

137
00:12:06,852 --> 00:12:08,145
Are you a stalker?

138
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:09,813
Are you jealous of Seol-ah?

139
00:12:09,896 --> 00:12:14,568
If you so much as follow her around
or harass her, you will regret it.

140
00:12:18,947 --> 00:12:20,699
[chuckles]

141
00:12:21,491 --> 00:12:23,618
All I wanted to do was scare her.

142
00:12:24,703 --> 00:12:26,288
I never thought that would happen.

143
00:12:27,456 --> 00:12:30,417
Then, where were you at
the time of Kim Yun-ji's fall?

144
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,960
I was at the party!

145
00:12:32,043 --> 00:12:36,131
I was shocked too, so I stayed
with the others to see what was going on.

146
00:12:38,884 --> 00:12:39,885
[sighs]

147
00:12:41,761 --> 00:12:42,762
[sighs]

148
00:12:50,312 --> 00:12:53,106
I honestly thought I was going to die.

149
00:12:53,190 --> 00:12:55,859
[sighs] How the hell did
Seol-ah stick it out in there?

150
00:12:55,942 --> 00:12:57,110
Oh, geez.

151
00:12:57,694 --> 00:13:02,574
Oh, wow. This is the first time
a consignor's died on me.

152
00:13:03,158 --> 00:13:05,410
I thought this year
was already bad enough.

153
00:13:06,578 --> 00:13:09,080
So what do we need to check legally?

154
00:13:09,998 --> 00:13:13,793
The consignment contract clearly
states that Royal Auction

155
00:13:13,877 --> 00:13:18,173
is responsible for securely storing the
painting until the owner comes forward.

156
00:13:18,256 --> 00:13:22,511
So, you're saying we can keep the painting
until the owner shows up. Is that right?

157
00:13:22,594 --> 00:13:23,720
Yes, ma'am.

158
00:13:23,803 --> 00:13:28,183
It's highly likely that the case will go
to court, so it'll probably take a while.

159
00:13:28,266 --> 00:13:29,392
Hmm.

160
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:33,146
Oh, ma'am, you need to see this.

161
00:13:33,897 --> 00:13:36,316
Ms. Han had this in her possession.

162
00:13:36,399 --> 00:13:37,400
Hmm.

163
00:13:40,237 --> 00:13:42,677
LIST OF CHAIR KIM'S PROPERTIES
REGISTERED UNDER BORROWED NAMES

164
00:13:43,031 --> 00:13:45,450
Looks like
you've got nothing better to do.

165
00:13:45,534 --> 00:13:47,911
I gave you everything
and you're still digging into this?

166
00:13:47,994 --> 00:13:52,123
If you can't replace the Stiller piece,
then you'll end up in Busan too.

167
00:13:52,207 --> 00:13:54,000
[stammers] Ma'am, but…

168
00:13:54,626 --> 00:13:55,627
Sure.

169
00:13:57,045 --> 00:13:58,547
[sighs]

170
00:13:59,381 --> 00:14:02,008
RECIPIENT: HAN SEO-YUL

171
00:14:02,092 --> 00:14:03,468
This looks like their base.

172
00:14:03,552 --> 00:14:05,136
Han Seo-yul, who caused the accident,

173
00:14:05,220 --> 00:14:06,805
might be living with Ju Hyun-su.

174
00:14:07,389 --> 00:14:10,684
[exclaims] I knew it.
Mr. Cha, you've got such good instinct!

175
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:14,187
I mean, you noticed the
same pattern as your sister's accident.

176
00:14:15,146 --> 00:14:19,025
Ha! These bastards were
totally in on it together! [Clicks tongue]

177
00:14:19,109 --> 00:14:20,694
What about the paintings?

178
00:14:21,528 --> 00:14:24,257
There were signs that the paintings
were moved to an empty store space.

179
00:14:24,281 --> 00:14:26,700
They must've been moved to
a more discreet location.

180
00:14:26,783 --> 00:14:27,784
[sighs]

181
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:31,204
Thank God we held the
Stiller piece before it disappeared.

182
00:14:32,539 --> 00:14:34,165
What's going to happen with that?

183
00:14:34,249 --> 00:14:35,917
The owner is dead.

184
00:14:36,001 --> 00:14:38,044
They'll go through
the inheritance process.

185
00:14:39,504 --> 00:14:41,590
I checked with the client's lawyer,

186
00:14:42,215 --> 00:14:45,760
and a designated recipient had already
been named in the event of his death.

187
00:14:46,428 --> 00:14:50,015
There's no way Han Seol-ah's
tangled up in this too, right?

188
00:14:54,227 --> 00:14:55,228
Oh, no way.

189
00:15:06,865 --> 00:15:08,259
CERTIFICATE OF TESTAMENTARY GIFT
OF ARTWORK

190
00:15:08,283 --> 00:15:10,163
ARTICLE 1
(TESTATOR AND BENEFICIARY INFORMATION)

191
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:14,039
TESTATOR: PAEK JUN-BEOM
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

192
00:15:25,508 --> 00:15:27,844
Why do you hate Han Seol-ah so much?

193
00:15:28,762 --> 00:15:32,223
When I was little, I used to like her.

194
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:38,855
Ever since I was six,
my brother meant everything to me.

195
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:40,607
[both panting]

196
00:15:40,690 --> 00:15:41,691
[yelps]

197
00:15:43,109 --> 00:15:45,029
- [young Eun-hye] No! [Whimpers]
- [grunts, groans]

198
00:15:50,241 --> 00:15:51,701
Get up, Do Eun-hyuk.

199
00:15:57,707 --> 00:15:58,708
[breathes shakily]

200
00:16:03,213 --> 00:16:04,255
Get up.

201
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:08,843
[groans]

202
00:16:14,265 --> 00:16:15,642
- Eun-hye.
- Yes.

203
00:16:15,725 --> 00:16:18,269
Please go tell your brother
to come eat with us.

204
00:16:18,353 --> 00:16:19,354
Okay!

205
00:16:42,377 --> 00:16:47,340
<i>The woman Do Eun-hyuk had his eyes
on his whole life was Han Seol-ah.</i>

206
00:16:48,466 --> 00:16:52,595
I was fine with him loving her
more than me, his own sister,

207
00:16:52,679 --> 00:16:54,305
as long as he was happy with her.

208
00:16:55,724 --> 00:16:57,434
[scoffs] But…

209
00:16:59,102 --> 00:17:01,563
It made me angry to
watch him get nothing in return

210
00:17:01,646 --> 00:17:04,399
and just be used over and over again,
like an idiot.

211
00:17:06,818 --> 00:17:08,737
So I thought if I
exposed who she really was,

212
00:17:08,820 --> 00:17:10,822
my brother would finally give up on her.

213
00:17:11,489 --> 00:17:16,578
That she wasn't just cursed with bad luck,
but a witch who kills people.

214
00:17:18,413 --> 00:17:20,582
So, Han Seol-ah is a witch?

215
00:17:24,252 --> 00:17:28,757
And yet your brother would still do
anything and everything for her, right?

216
00:17:33,470 --> 00:17:34,596
Eun-hye.

217
00:17:35,472 --> 00:17:37,265
[sighs] Brother.

218
00:17:37,807 --> 00:17:40,059
Get up. Let's go.

219
00:17:56,451 --> 00:17:57,452
[sighs]

220
00:17:58,995 --> 00:18:00,997
Why aren't you saying anything?

221
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,207
Huh?

222
00:18:03,208 --> 00:18:05,794
Why aren't you
getting angry or scolding me?

223
00:18:11,841 --> 00:18:13,009
Let's go eat.

224
00:18:13,092 --> 00:18:14,511
What would you like?

225
00:18:16,596 --> 00:18:18,473
Shouldn't I be getting a nice meal
after that?

226
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:20,517
And why is that?

227
00:18:21,684 --> 00:18:23,937
All you did was get
questioned as a witness.

228
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:27,148
Well, I just never want to
come back to the police station.

229
00:18:27,232 --> 00:18:30,652
I did nothing wrong, but it's still scary…

230
00:18:37,325 --> 00:18:38,618
I'm sorry.

231
00:18:42,539 --> 00:18:44,123
I'm sorry for everything.

232
00:18:45,458 --> 00:18:49,170
Then buy me a steak.

233
00:18:49,254 --> 00:18:52,048
Not pork, good beef. The best kind.

234
00:18:53,883 --> 00:18:55,093
Let's go.

235
00:19:04,018 --> 00:19:05,270
Those addresses…

236
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:07,730
You actually checked them all?

237
00:19:08,731 --> 00:19:10,525
Chair Kim's properties.

238
00:19:12,235 --> 00:19:14,237
I'm looking into them one by one.

239
00:19:15,196 --> 00:19:16,823
How's Eun-hye doing?

240
00:19:16,906 --> 00:19:19,284
I heard she bawled her eyes
out at the police.

241
00:19:20,368 --> 00:19:22,120
I was so nervous I started shaking,

242
00:19:22,203 --> 00:19:24,247
so imagine how scared she was.

243
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:25,748
It's all my fault.

244
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:29,711
She looks like an adult on the outside,
but inside she's still a kid.

245
00:19:30,295 --> 00:19:31,921
I should've been more caring.

246
00:19:32,881 --> 00:19:35,341
Maybe don't be too harsh on Eun-hye.

247
00:19:35,425 --> 00:19:37,093
She was just looking out for her brother.

248
00:19:37,176 --> 00:19:41,180
That's right. When you love someone,
you want to protect them.

249
00:19:41,848 --> 00:19:44,475
I lashed out at Kim Yun-ji
the day she died.

250
00:19:45,727 --> 00:19:47,270
You did?

251
00:19:47,353 --> 00:19:50,106
It looked like she was
giving you a hard time at work.

252
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:54,402
I'd been planning to give her a piece of
my mind and waiting for the right moment.

253
00:19:54,485 --> 00:19:56,654
Sorry I stuck my nose in.

254
00:19:56,738 --> 00:20:01,326
I kept thinking I should tell you,
but I just couldn't open my mouth, so…

255
00:20:02,035 --> 00:20:03,828
Yeah, but you shouldn't have
gotten involved.

256
00:20:03,912 --> 00:20:05,997
[sighing] I know…

257
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:08,791
Thank you.

258
00:20:11,628 --> 00:20:15,423
It feels good knowing
that someone's always got my back.

259
00:20:16,799 --> 00:20:21,095
You know, when we were kids,
you two always stood up for me.

260
00:20:21,721 --> 00:20:24,140
When kids bad-mouthed me or picked on me,

261
00:20:25,308 --> 00:20:28,394
Eun-hyuk would beat them up,
and you would humiliate them.

262
00:20:29,062 --> 00:20:31,105
Sorry, and thank you.

263
00:20:31,189 --> 00:20:32,273
Even if it's too late.

264
00:20:33,191 --> 00:20:35,985
Hey, why are you
suddenly acting like this?

265
00:20:36,486 --> 00:20:38,363
Now, I feel even worse.

266
00:20:38,988 --> 00:20:39,989
[chuckles]

267
00:20:40,073 --> 00:20:41,491
[sniffles]

268
00:20:41,991 --> 00:20:44,077
Don't cry. You'll ruin your makeup.

269
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,328
[sniffles]

270
00:20:45,411 --> 00:20:48,373
I only did it
because I wanted to protect you.

271
00:20:48,456 --> 00:20:50,124
You know how I feel, right?

272
00:20:51,459 --> 00:20:52,585
- [chuckles]
- [sniffles]

273
00:20:55,922 --> 00:20:57,590
[phone buzzing]

274
00:20:57,674 --> 00:21:00,134
CHA WOO-SEOK

275
00:21:11,104 --> 00:21:13,106
[line ringing]

276
00:21:16,818 --> 00:21:18,820
[phone buzzing continues]

277
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:36,004
[line rings, stops]

278
00:21:36,087 --> 00:21:37,797
[voicemail] <i>Your call cannot be connected.</i>

279
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:40,008
- <i>You will be directed to voicemail…</i>
- [phone beeps]

280
00:21:40,091 --> 00:21:41,092
[sighs]

281
00:21:45,221 --> 00:21:46,581
[Eun-hyuk] <i>Did you really mean it?</i>

282
00:21:50,351 --> 00:21:53,563
When you told me
I should stop focusing on you.

283
00:21:55,189 --> 00:21:56,941
When we were kids,

284
00:21:58,735 --> 00:22:01,571
I thought we'd go to college together,

285
00:22:02,447 --> 00:22:05,408
and then end up being
something special to each other.

286
00:22:06,492 --> 00:22:11,372
But then I watched as you always
made sure to keep your distance from me,

287
00:22:11,456 --> 00:22:15,793
and I realized the furthest
you'd ever let me in, was as a friend.

288
00:22:16,544 --> 00:22:20,548
If my past was a burden even to you,

289
00:22:21,549 --> 00:22:23,760
then who in this world
could I ever be with?

290
00:22:24,469 --> 00:22:26,179
But, it's not like that.

291
00:22:26,262 --> 00:22:28,723
Do you know why I dated Su-ho?

292
00:22:29,974 --> 00:22:31,851
He had even less than I did.

293
00:22:32,435 --> 00:22:34,103
He needed me

294
00:22:34,187 --> 00:22:37,982
enough that even someone like me
could feel pity for him,

295
00:22:38,066 --> 00:22:39,984
so I couldn't just turn away.

296
00:22:42,236 --> 00:22:46,157
So, that means you chose Lee Su-ho
instead of me?

297
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:48,284
I didn't want to lose you.

298
00:22:49,118 --> 00:22:52,038
It was also easier
to be with someone who liked me.

299
00:22:53,456 --> 00:22:54,957
I was a coward.

300
00:22:55,041 --> 00:22:57,251
[inhales deeply]
What about the other guys?

301
00:22:57,960 --> 00:23:00,046
Did you date them
just 'cause they liked you?

302
00:23:00,129 --> 00:23:03,883
I hated being alone,
and I wanted to start a family.

303
00:23:05,551 --> 00:23:12,016
I thought I was a very strong person,
but I guess I was wrong.

304
00:23:13,434 --> 00:23:15,269
You don't have to be so strong.

305
00:23:16,771 --> 00:23:18,231
Just be yourself

306
00:23:19,524 --> 00:23:21,234
and live your life.

307
00:23:22,276 --> 00:23:25,154
Lee Su-ho legally died twice
because of me.

308
00:23:25,988 --> 00:23:30,993
I guess your decision of not becoming
involved with me was the right one.

309
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:33,830
No, Seol-ah, that's…

310
00:23:42,922 --> 00:23:43,923
[sighs]

311
00:23:51,222 --> 00:23:52,974
GANGHA POLICE STATION

312
00:23:53,057 --> 00:23:56,018
Chair Kim of Royal Auction
prepared the champagne herself?

313
00:23:56,102 --> 00:23:57,742
What's her relationship with Han Seol-ah?

314
00:23:57,770 --> 00:23:59,730
Is she only just her boss?

315
00:23:59,814 --> 00:24:01,566
Paek Jun-beom was a VIP client,

316
00:24:01,649 --> 00:24:04,944
so Chair Kim had Han Seol-ah
assigned to manage him.

317
00:24:05,027 --> 00:24:07,655
Check if there's an insurance
policy involved in this case.

318
00:24:07,738 --> 00:24:10,158
Let's see if it follows the same pattern.

319
00:24:10,241 --> 00:24:12,660
I still have suspicions about Do Eun-hyuk.

320
00:24:13,327 --> 00:24:15,955
But we checked all of
his alibis last time.

321
00:24:16,038 --> 00:24:18,918
Woo-seok's accident happened while
Do Eun-hyuk was being questioned here,

322
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,169
but that was actually instigated
by Lee Su-ho,

323
00:24:21,252 --> 00:24:23,504
so it has nothing to do with Do Eun-hyuk.

324
00:24:24,338 --> 00:24:26,257
While interrogating Do Eun-hye,

325
00:24:26,340 --> 00:24:29,635
I got the sense that he would do
anything Han Seol-ah asked him to do.

326
00:24:30,469 --> 00:24:31,470
[sighs]

327
00:24:31,554 --> 00:24:35,016
Let's start by tracing his movements
on the day Lee Su-ho died.

328
00:24:45,193 --> 00:24:46,777
You're still working?

329
00:24:48,446 --> 00:24:51,157
Wow, how do you take photos like this?

330
00:24:51,824 --> 00:24:53,826
Do you have to dive in with the model?

331
00:24:54,619 --> 00:24:56,621
There's an underwater studio.

332
00:24:56,704 --> 00:24:59,123
Sometimes I shoot at a free diving center,

333
00:24:59,999 --> 00:25:02,043
and other times I go out to the ocean.

334
00:25:05,338 --> 00:25:08,466
It's very cool, but isn't it dangerous?

335
00:25:09,467 --> 00:25:11,886
You'd have to be good at scuba diving,
I guess.

336
00:25:13,262 --> 00:25:15,598
No major accidents so far.

337
00:25:17,099 --> 00:25:19,518
But, what brings you here?

338
00:25:20,436 --> 00:25:25,274
On the day Paek Jun-beom died, you were
working at that Royal Auction event?

339
00:25:25,858 --> 00:25:26,859
I was.

340
00:25:27,568 --> 00:25:30,363
Did you see Paek Jun-beom…

341
00:25:30,446 --> 00:25:32,615
I mean Lee Su-ho collapsing?

342
00:25:32,698 --> 00:25:34,242
Everyone saw it.

343
00:25:37,536 --> 00:25:39,622
Where did you go after the event that day?

344
00:25:42,333 --> 00:25:43,626
I went to Cheongun.

345
00:25:43,709 --> 00:25:45,294
I have my personal studio there.

346
00:25:46,337 --> 00:25:48,923
Didn't you say you usually
go there on the weekends?

347
00:25:49,006 --> 00:25:52,802
So, why go all the way there
on a weekday at such a late hour?

348
00:25:52,885 --> 00:25:55,304
I had a project
that needed to be finished.

349
00:25:57,431 --> 00:26:00,476
Can you prove that you were in Cheongun
the night of the murder?

350
00:26:02,478 --> 00:26:03,938
How would you like me to prove it?

351
00:26:04,021 --> 00:26:07,024
With your dashcam footage.
Should be more than enough.

352
00:26:07,817 --> 00:26:09,902
There's a camera in front of my studio.

353
00:26:09,986 --> 00:26:11,306
Do you want me to check that too?

354
00:26:11,821 --> 00:26:13,990
Well, it'd be great
if you could submit both.

355
00:26:14,073 --> 00:26:15,491
Sure, no problem.

356
00:26:32,633 --> 00:26:34,885
Phone bid, $70,000.

357
00:26:34,969 --> 00:26:36,721
Current highest is 70,000.

358
00:26:36,804 --> 00:26:40,266
Do I have a bid of 73,500?

359
00:26:40,349 --> 00:26:42,268
$73,500, confirmed.

360
00:26:42,351 --> 00:26:44,562
That's the highest bid
on the floor right now.

361
00:26:44,645 --> 00:26:47,940
Do I hear $77,000? 77,000...

362
00:26:48,024 --> 00:26:49,233
I'm withdrawing my bid.

363
00:26:50,735 --> 00:26:51,861
I've had a change of heart.

364
00:26:51,944 --> 00:26:53,154
What?

365
00:26:55,573 --> 00:26:57,450
The flow's been broken.

366
00:26:58,159 --> 00:27:00,095
Dozens of people are
waiting for you to captivate them.

367
00:27:00,119 --> 00:27:01,704
What are you gonna do?

368
00:27:01,787 --> 00:27:05,541
An auctioneer isn't just
someone who calls out bids.

369
00:27:05,624 --> 00:27:08,794
They convince people of
the value of the artwork.

370
00:27:08,878 --> 00:27:11,505
No matter how much the crowd wavers,
you have to stay grounded.

371
00:27:13,090 --> 00:27:15,217
- [sighs]
- You have to trust yourself.

372
00:27:16,177 --> 00:27:18,763
Yes, the withdrawal of
the on-floor bid has been confirmed.

373
00:27:18,846 --> 00:27:22,391
The current highest is 70,000
from a phone bidder.

374
00:27:22,475 --> 00:27:25,269
Now confirming $73,500.

375
00:27:25,353 --> 00:27:26,395
No more bids?

376
00:27:26,479 --> 00:27:30,274
I will call it three times and then
I will proceed to close the bidding.

377
00:27:30,858 --> 00:27:35,112
73,500.73,500.73,500.

378
00:27:35,196 --> 00:27:36,655
Any more bids?

379
00:27:37,698 --> 00:27:40,785
And sold for 70,000.

380
00:27:45,539 --> 00:27:48,000
[melancholy music playing]

381
00:29:10,624 --> 00:29:12,042
[phone buzzing]

382
00:29:17,339 --> 00:29:18,340
Hello?

383
00:29:18,424 --> 00:29:21,886
[secretary] <i>Ms. Han, I'm calling from</i>
<i>the secretary's office at Your Home.</i>

384
00:29:23,387 --> 00:29:24,805
How can I help you?

385
00:29:25,347 --> 00:29:27,933
<i>I need to discuss an inheritance matter
with you.</i>

386
00:29:31,645 --> 00:29:32,831
YOUR HOME LEGAL TEAM
ATTORNEY KIM JUN-SEONG

387
00:29:32,855 --> 00:29:35,941
I am the attorney handling the execution
of the late Paek Jun-beom's will.

388
00:29:37,318 --> 00:29:40,529
Mr. Paek left something for you,
Ms. Han Seol-ah.

389
00:29:40,613 --> 00:29:41,947
He left it for me?

390
00:29:42,490 --> 00:29:47,203
You have inherited a painting.
One painted by Emil Stiller.

391
00:29:47,286 --> 00:29:49,497
He insured it prior to the auction
and designated you,

392
00:29:49,580 --> 00:29:53,709
Ms. Han Seol-ah, as the beneficiary
in the event of his death.

393
00:29:54,210 --> 00:29:57,588
I haven't heard anything about this
and I never agreed to it.

394
00:29:57,671 --> 00:30:00,424
A bequest doesn't require
the beneficiary's approval.

395
00:30:02,468 --> 00:30:05,387
I guess he wanted to keep it a secret.

396
00:30:06,388 --> 00:30:10,017
[secretary] Mr. Paek had been experiencing
complications from the Syria incident,

397
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:13,395
so he made preparations
in case anything happened.

398
00:30:21,070 --> 00:30:23,614
So is this really
Ms. Han's last auction here?

399
00:30:23,697 --> 00:30:27,034
They're transferring her to Busan,
but it means they're pushing her out.

400
00:30:27,743 --> 00:30:29,912
Oh, that's what it means.

401
00:30:29,995 --> 00:30:32,498
Honestly, does this make any sense to you,
Tae-seok?

402
00:30:32,581 --> 00:30:35,042
- No, it doesn't!
- [sighs] Sang-mi on the main stage?

403
00:30:35,793 --> 00:30:37,753
[sighs] We're at the same level now

404
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:40,089
but soon she'll be my supervisor.

405
00:30:40,172 --> 00:30:42,675
I show off all the skills,
and someone else gets promoted!

406
00:30:42,758 --> 00:30:44,760
Hmm, skills?

407
00:30:45,553 --> 00:30:47,805
I don't remember seeing her show off any.

408
00:30:47,888 --> 00:30:48,889
[Na-hee] What?

409
00:30:50,432 --> 00:30:51,433
[elevator dings]

410
00:30:57,523 --> 00:30:58,774
[sighs]

411
00:30:59,525 --> 00:31:01,110
Are you still seeing Han Seol-ah?

412
00:31:02,987 --> 00:31:04,947
Looks like she's about to get fired.

413
00:31:07,324 --> 00:31:08,784
I'm here for work.

414
00:31:09,285 --> 00:31:10,995
[scoffs] Nice excuse.

415
00:31:12,121 --> 00:31:13,455
Any progress in the case?

416
00:31:16,292 --> 00:31:18,002
What? You're not going to tell me?

417
00:31:18,544 --> 00:31:20,504
I don't think
you're telling me everything either.

418
00:31:22,881 --> 00:31:23,966
Let's talk later then.

419
00:31:24,049 --> 00:31:25,426
Why?

420
00:31:30,848 --> 00:31:32,057
[sighs]

421
00:31:35,561 --> 00:31:37,563
[footsteps approaching]

422
00:31:43,277 --> 00:31:44,278
[sighs]

423
00:31:45,154 --> 00:31:46,655
Sorry for coming unannounced.

424
00:31:49,575 --> 00:31:50,826
I tried calling, but…

425
00:31:52,036 --> 00:31:54,997
Do you want me to take a guess
why you're here?

426
00:31:58,417 --> 00:31:59,835
The Stiller painting.

427
00:32:01,503 --> 00:32:02,504
[sighs]

428
00:32:24,943 --> 00:32:26,195
Ask away.

429
00:32:27,655 --> 00:32:29,823
Aren't you here
because you wanted to ask me something?

430
00:32:30,908 --> 00:32:36,330
Why Su-ho left such an expensive painting
to me, whether I already knew everything,

431
00:32:37,456 --> 00:32:39,041
or whether I caused him to do it.

432
00:32:42,044 --> 00:32:44,213
It's unlikely to become yours though,

433
00:32:45,005 --> 00:32:46,924
it depends on how they see it.

434
00:32:47,549 --> 00:32:49,843
If it's a bequest from Paek Jun-beom,

435
00:32:50,427 --> 00:32:52,262
or if it's from Lee Su-ho.

436
00:32:54,515 --> 00:32:56,308
You came here just to say that?

437
00:32:57,559 --> 00:33:00,354
To tell me the Stiller painting
can't be mine?

438
00:33:03,107 --> 00:33:04,566
I wanted to see you…

439
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:11,240
Because I was worried.

440
00:33:22,084 --> 00:33:25,379
It's a special clause in the will.
The police aren't aware of it yet.

441
00:33:25,462 --> 00:33:26,922
We can't stall much,

442
00:33:27,005 --> 00:33:29,192
but we can buy some time
until the real culprit is revealed...

443
00:33:29,216 --> 00:33:30,217
No need for that.

444
00:33:30,968 --> 00:33:33,637
Just give the police
all the information they want.

445
00:33:33,721 --> 00:33:36,348
Then Han Seol-ah becomes
the prime suspect again.

446
00:33:37,057 --> 00:33:41,478
Maybe that's just what
Su-ho wanted exactly.

447
00:33:42,771 --> 00:33:47,735
I don't believe he left me the painting
because he actually wanted me to have it.

448
00:33:49,111 --> 00:33:51,071
- [sighs]
- I'll say this again.

449
00:33:52,114 --> 00:33:53,615
You're in danger too, Woo-seok.

450
00:33:54,199 --> 00:33:59,580
The culprit has never once targeted me,
but the man by my side.

451
00:34:10,299 --> 00:34:11,675
Then protect me.

452
00:34:13,343 --> 00:34:15,387
Don't push me away because you're scared,

453
00:34:16,180 --> 00:34:17,389
and please don't run.

454
00:34:20,058 --> 00:34:21,769
Stay right by my side…

455
00:34:24,229 --> 00:34:25,731
And keep me safe.

456
00:34:30,903 --> 00:34:31,904
[sighs]

457
00:34:55,219 --> 00:34:56,220
[lock clicks]

458
00:34:58,430 --> 00:34:59,515
[line rings]

459
00:35:00,474 --> 00:35:01,809
I need to see you.

460
00:35:04,728 --> 00:35:05,729
[line clicks]

461
00:35:06,939 --> 00:35:09,942
LIST OF CHAIR KIM'S PROPERTIES
REGISTERED UNDER BORROWED NAMES

462
00:35:10,651 --> 00:35:12,694
I was actually about to head over to you.

463
00:35:13,529 --> 00:35:14,530
TERRACE DE VILLA

464
00:35:14,613 --> 00:35:16,573
While going through
Chair Kim's properties,

465
00:35:16,657 --> 00:35:18,426
and looking for a suitable place
to hide Taemyung's paintings…

466
00:35:18,450 --> 00:35:19,910
HYUN-SU'S FRUIT

467
00:35:25,332 --> 00:35:28,669
Ju Hyun-su, Chair Kim's henchman.

468
00:35:30,462 --> 00:35:33,549
I've seen him going in and out
of Chair Kim's office here,

469
00:35:33,632 --> 00:35:35,843
and I thought I should let you know.

470
00:35:37,052 --> 00:35:39,263
So, we've been after the same person?

471
00:35:39,763 --> 00:35:41,515
If we find Taemyung's paintings,

472
00:35:41,598 --> 00:35:45,185
we'll uncover everything
that Chair Kim and Ju Hyun-su did,

473
00:35:45,936 --> 00:35:51,400
and finally you'll be able to reveal the
truth about what happened to your sister.

474
00:35:57,865 --> 00:36:00,909
There was evidence
that the paintings were moved here.

475
00:36:00,993 --> 00:36:03,912
I think the space was used
when the paintings were swapped.

476
00:36:04,413 --> 00:36:07,791
Chair Kim deals with
risky business elsewhere,

477
00:36:07,875 --> 00:36:09,543
and once it's finally safe,

478
00:36:09,626 --> 00:36:11,503
she moves it to the secret vault.

479
00:36:12,754 --> 00:36:14,214
Then the paintings are…

480
00:36:16,592 --> 00:36:19,303
Among the warehouses
that the company rents,

481
00:36:19,386 --> 00:36:21,889
there's one that
the employees can't access.

482
00:36:22,389 --> 00:36:25,517
That warehouse has been reserved
for Chair Kim's personal use.

483
00:36:26,059 --> 00:36:28,020
The storage unit
where that accident happened.

484
00:36:30,355 --> 00:36:32,107
Where Paek Jun-beom was?

485
00:36:58,926 --> 00:37:02,054
Why call me
to such an expensive place, huh?

486
00:37:03,347 --> 00:37:05,599
I was hoping for some food
cooked by you, ma'am.

487
00:37:09,102 --> 00:37:11,188
An insurance investigator is on the case,

488
00:37:12,022 --> 00:37:15,776
and Ms. Han is working with him,
and she's determined to screw me over.

489
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:21,448
[sighs]

490
00:37:22,199 --> 00:37:24,034
What are you doing
about the Taemyung piece?

491
00:37:27,913 --> 00:37:29,122
There's no need to worry.

492
00:37:29,706 --> 00:37:31,625
What can they really do about it?

493
00:37:32,417 --> 00:37:34,294
There's no hard evidence anywhere.

494
00:37:34,378 --> 00:37:36,129
And if they manage to find the paintings?

495
00:37:36,213 --> 00:37:40,217
Don't you realize when that happens,
it will all be over?

496
00:37:41,927 --> 00:37:44,680
They're safely stored,
so don't worry, okay?

497
00:37:46,014 --> 00:37:47,015
Hmm.

498
00:37:47,975 --> 00:37:51,228
It's too risky where they are.
Move them to my vault now.

499
00:37:53,563 --> 00:37:54,773
Okay.

500
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:56,668
[engine starts]

501
00:39:26,573 --> 00:39:28,450
The art storage has just become available,

502
00:39:28,533 --> 00:39:31,578
so you can go ahead
and set up a new contract with us.

503
00:39:35,248 --> 00:39:37,529
Are you saying there were paintings
stored here until now?

504
00:39:37,876 --> 00:39:40,170
[receptionist] Yes,
someone canceled their contract.

505
00:39:40,670 --> 00:39:43,590
Are there any other
art-specific storage units here on site?

506
00:39:43,673 --> 00:39:46,551
This is the only space
designed specifically for art.

507
00:39:47,427 --> 00:39:49,513
Was there an issue with the storage unit?

508
00:39:50,097 --> 00:39:51,098
From what I understand,

509
00:39:51,181 --> 00:39:53,558
the owner retrieved them
due to personal reasons.

510
00:40:00,607 --> 00:40:04,194
The paintings that were here
definitely belong to the Taemyung Group.

511
00:40:05,237 --> 00:40:07,656
[sighs] The truck we saw earlier

512
00:40:13,703 --> 00:40:16,123
[sighs] we should've checked it.

513
00:40:16,206 --> 00:40:18,458
That leaves us with just one possibility.

514
00:40:18,542 --> 00:40:20,502
How much time do we have
until your auction?

515
00:40:21,294 --> 00:40:22,295
One week.

516
00:40:23,463 --> 00:40:25,257
That's all the time we have to get in.

517
00:40:25,799 --> 00:40:27,300
They're in Chair Kim's vault.

518
00:40:28,301 --> 00:40:29,301
[sighs]

519
00:40:29,344 --> 00:40:30,929
[door opening]

520
00:41:10,177 --> 00:41:12,179
I heard they've been pressuring you
to resign.

521
00:41:13,263 --> 00:41:15,557
From Chair Kim's perspective, I get it.

522
00:41:16,224 --> 00:41:17,517
What boss would want an employee

523
00:41:17,601 --> 00:41:19,644
constantly at the police station?

524
00:41:20,395 --> 00:41:23,315
Keeping your feelings hidden
right beside your enemy…

525
00:41:24,316 --> 00:41:25,942
That couldn't have been easy.

526
00:41:27,444 --> 00:41:28,445
There were…

527
00:41:30,071 --> 00:41:31,656
Times I wavered too…

528
00:41:33,825 --> 00:41:37,245
Because I couldn't accept
hating the person I was supposed to hate.

529
00:41:40,123 --> 00:41:41,124
[sighs]

530
00:41:48,548 --> 00:41:50,342
I saw that a lot while investigating.

531
00:41:51,384 --> 00:41:55,055
Parents who blind their own
children just to collect insurance money

532
00:41:56,598 --> 00:41:59,226
and kids who protect their parents
even though they're monsters.

533
00:42:00,101 --> 00:42:04,773
I guess what you feel towards Chair Kim
is something like that.

534
00:42:07,317 --> 00:42:11,279
Woo-seok, how do you know all of that?

535
00:42:13,782 --> 00:42:15,242
Because I was a survivor too.

536
00:42:47,816 --> 00:42:48,817
[door opens]

537
00:42:51,152 --> 00:42:52,445
[door closes]

538
00:42:52,529 --> 00:42:54,990
[grunts] What took you so long?
I'm seriously starving.

539
00:42:55,073 --> 00:42:57,409
I couldn't eat anything
since this isn't my place.

540
00:43:03,748 --> 00:43:05,834
Wow. This two-shot.

541
00:43:06,793 --> 00:43:10,088
Very nice.
Your visuals match really well together.

542
00:43:18,179 --> 00:43:19,180
Here we go.

543
00:43:19,264 --> 00:43:21,701
This is a subcontractor that worked
with the Royal Auction architect.

544
00:43:21,725 --> 00:43:24,519
Companies like this usually have
pretty low security.

545
00:43:24,602 --> 00:43:29,232
The Royal Auction building
was completed on July 15, 2017.

546
00:43:30,066 --> 00:43:30,984
2016-2017

547
00:43:31,067 --> 00:43:34,654
These look like the blueprint files
exchanged from 2016 to 2017.

548
00:43:34,738 --> 00:43:35,739
Oh…

549
00:43:36,614 --> 00:43:37,782
INDIVIDUAL HALL

550
00:43:37,866 --> 00:43:39,075
PROFESSIONAL BLDG

551
00:43:39,159 --> 00:43:40,368
ROYAL AUCTION

552
00:43:44,122 --> 00:43:46,124
ROYAL AUCTION_13F (CHAIRMAN'S SUITE).PDF

553
00:43:50,503 --> 00:43:51,796
Found it.

554
00:43:55,258 --> 00:43:56,384
Just as I thought.

555
00:43:57,302 --> 00:44:00,472
It's this empty space behind
the kitchen wall in Chair Kim's office.

556
00:44:01,097 --> 00:44:02,515
The space is pretty big.

557
00:44:03,183 --> 00:44:05,101
Could there really be a secret vault?

558
00:44:05,602 --> 00:44:09,939
It's close by, easy to manage, and there
are no security cameras on that floor.

559
00:44:18,198 --> 00:44:20,450
Wait, don't tell me
we're going to sneak in there.

560
00:44:40,553 --> 00:44:41,989
CORNERSTONE
HERE BEGINS A NEW ERA OF ART

561
00:44:42,013 --> 00:44:43,157
BUILDING NAME: ROYAL AUCTION BUILDING

562
00:44:43,181 --> 00:44:45,642
[Seol-ah] <i>Chair Kim has a password</i>
<i>she always uses.</i>

563
00:44:49,938 --> 00:44:52,482
<i>One, seven, zero, seven, one, five.</i>

564
00:45:01,908 --> 00:45:02,909
[gasps]

565
00:45:03,785 --> 00:45:05,120
Congrats, Ms. Han!

566
00:45:06,162 --> 00:45:09,165
Oh, my. Oh, oh. Hey, hey, hey.

567
00:45:09,249 --> 00:45:10,250
So…

568
00:45:11,126 --> 00:45:13,503
Mr. Paek left behind a gift for you, huh?

569
00:45:14,921 --> 00:45:18,049
I heard that the Stiller piece
is yours now.

570
00:45:20,885 --> 00:45:23,012
I have no intention of accepting it.

571
00:45:23,096 --> 00:45:24,431
Are you crazy?

572
00:45:25,056 --> 00:45:27,267
The guy who died
isn't the real Paek Jun-beom.

573
00:45:27,350 --> 00:45:29,018
He was impersonating him.

574
00:45:29,602 --> 00:45:33,064
It's not even his, so how could he
have the right to leave it to me?

575
00:45:33,148 --> 00:45:36,234
Don't worry. I already checked everything
with a law firm.

576
00:45:36,317 --> 00:45:39,737
And legally, there's a very high chance
you'll get it.

577
00:45:39,821 --> 00:45:42,740
And if it doesn't work out,
we'll file a lawsuit.

578
00:45:42,824 --> 00:45:44,451
I'll cover all the costs.

579
00:45:46,786 --> 00:45:50,623
Aren't you investing too much
on an employee you're about to let go?

580
00:45:51,249 --> 00:45:52,250
When did I say that?

581
00:45:52,333 --> 00:45:56,212
I only told you to go take it easy
at the Busan office.

582
00:45:56,296 --> 00:45:57,547
I never said you were out.

583
00:45:57,630 --> 00:46:02,594
Besides, now that we're here, you don't
even have to go to Busan anymore.

584
00:46:02,677 --> 00:46:05,472
Your father can finally
rest easy now, huh?

585
00:46:05,555 --> 00:46:08,349
Looks like his daughter's
about to land on her feet.

586
00:46:12,437 --> 00:46:15,482
We haven't decided on the main piece
for the upcoming auction yet.

587
00:46:15,565 --> 00:46:17,859
Did you happen to see
the list I submitted?

588
00:46:26,326 --> 00:46:28,745
Song Hwan-ju's posthumous piece.

589
00:46:31,748 --> 00:46:34,167
It's his last work, never released before.

590
00:46:34,876 --> 00:46:38,713
When the world sees this,
it'll cause a huge stir, huh?

591
00:46:39,923 --> 00:46:40,965
This… How did you…

592
00:46:41,049 --> 00:46:44,302
This is a stand-in for the Stiller piece,
so it needs to make an impact.

593
00:46:45,261 --> 00:46:49,682
And it's the biggest card
I've been hiding under my sleeve.

594
00:46:51,893 --> 00:46:52,894
This is great.

595
00:46:54,145 --> 00:46:57,607
It will certainly generate
about as much buzz as the Stiller.

596
00:46:59,400 --> 00:47:02,695
It's quite the send-off
for my last auction.

597
00:47:07,659 --> 00:47:09,953
I'm offering you an opportunity,

598
00:47:11,538 --> 00:47:14,165
and you're still saying
this is your last one?

599
00:47:23,091 --> 00:47:24,818
COMMERCIAL INSURANCE COVERAGE
FOR MUSEUMS AND CULTURAL INSTITUTIONS

600
00:47:24,842 --> 00:47:28,054
INSURANCE POLICY
NAME: PAEK JUN-BEOM

601
00:47:29,639 --> 00:47:31,079
GROUNDS FOR RESCISSION OF THE POLICY

602
00:47:31,140 --> 00:47:33,060
CONSIGNOR: PAEK JUN-BEOM
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

603
00:47:33,685 --> 00:47:34,686
A bequest?

604
00:47:35,270 --> 00:47:37,772
It's a special clause
stating that if Paek Jun-beom dies,

605
00:47:37,855 --> 00:47:40,191
Han Seol-ah inherits
the Emil Stiller painting,

606
00:47:40,275 --> 00:47:42,193
and the insurance payout
goes to her as well.

607
00:47:42,277 --> 00:47:45,405
What? I heard it's gonna sell
for over $10 million.

608
00:47:45,488 --> 00:47:47,574
Does that mean
we're suspecting Han Seol-ah?

609
00:47:48,575 --> 00:47:49,993
That's a strong motive for murder.

610
00:47:51,995 --> 00:47:54,956
If Han Seol-ah is behind it,
she may have changed her pattern.

611
00:47:55,039 --> 00:47:58,793
When all those men died, she failed to
collect the insurance payouts.

612
00:47:58,876 --> 00:48:02,547
But now with the painting in the bequest,
it's different.

613
00:48:03,590 --> 00:48:05,174
She can make sure she gets the money.

614
00:48:05,842 --> 00:48:07,677
And the stakes are even higher now.

615
00:48:07,760 --> 00:48:10,597
Wait, but Paek Jun-beom was actually
Lee Su-ho, right?

616
00:48:10,680 --> 00:48:12,098
Can she still inherit it?

617
00:48:12,181 --> 00:48:14,642
I actually looked into it,
and it's a bit complicated.

618
00:48:14,726 --> 00:48:16,603
He lived under the identity of
Paek Jun-beom,

619
00:48:16,686 --> 00:48:19,046
but the painting could also be considered
Lee Su-ho's asset.

620
00:48:19,105 --> 00:48:20,898
There's room for a legal dispute.

621
00:48:20,982 --> 00:48:22,483
They'll have a lawsuit then.

622
00:48:24,277 --> 00:48:27,155
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

623
00:49:02,065 --> 00:49:04,859
I already put the tracker
on Chair Kim's car.

624
00:49:05,443 --> 00:49:06,819
Dr. Shin will be watching.

625
00:49:13,826 --> 00:49:16,621
Are you sure you'll be okay though?
Why don't I just do it...

626
00:49:16,704 --> 00:49:20,041
In the worst case, one of us will
stay behind and proceed with Plan B.

627
00:49:20,708 --> 00:49:21,709
If I get caught,

628
00:49:21,793 --> 00:49:24,003
I can just say I'm leaving
the company anyway.

629
00:49:24,087 --> 00:49:26,506
But if you get caught, our plan fails.

630
00:49:27,090 --> 00:49:28,091
[sighs]

631
00:49:28,633 --> 00:49:30,510
Just take pictures and get out right away.

632
00:49:41,396 --> 00:49:42,397
[device beeps]

633
00:49:44,232 --> 00:49:45,274
LIVE CAM
CANCEL / CONNECT

634
00:49:45,358 --> 00:49:46,859
CONNECTING…

635
00:50:26,858 --> 00:50:28,651
Chair Kim's on her way home right now.

636
00:50:28,735 --> 00:50:30,236
Be ready in case security shows up,

637
00:50:30,319 --> 00:50:32,196
and mark the entrance clearly.

638
00:51:43,726 --> 00:51:44,769
I'm in front of the door.

639
00:51:54,445 --> 00:51:57,114
[Seol-ah] <i>One, seven, zero,</i>
<i>seven, one, five.</i>

640
00:51:57,198 --> 00:51:58,407
[lock clicks]

641
00:52:16,717 --> 00:52:18,344
[Seol-ah] <i>I'm going in.</i>

642
00:52:18,427 --> 00:52:19,637
Be careful.

643
00:52:26,060 --> 00:52:27,061
[lock clicks]

644
00:52:33,901 --> 00:52:36,988
[gasps, sighs]

645
00:52:38,155 --> 00:52:39,740
I made it in.

646
00:52:44,078 --> 00:52:44,954
[static]

647
00:52:45,037 --> 00:52:46,205
[static continues]

648
00:52:47,081 --> 00:52:49,125
- Woo-seok?
- Seol-ah.

649
00:52:50,209 --> 00:52:51,335
Seol-ah?

650
00:52:57,216 --> 00:52:58,902
UNSTABLE CONNECTION, CHECK NETWORK
TRY AGAIN

651
00:52:58,926 --> 00:53:00,094
[phone buzzes]

652
00:53:04,223 --> 00:53:05,057
ACCESS GRANTED

653
00:53:05,141 --> 00:53:05,975
DOOR SECURED

654
00:53:06,058 --> 00:53:08,436
Is this an error? What is this?

655
00:53:27,705 --> 00:53:30,207
[Seol-ah] <i>Vanished Sensation</i>
by Fabien Leclerc

656
00:53:30,291 --> 00:53:33,377
is sold to Chairman Park Min-cheol
of the Taemyung Group.

657
00:53:36,130 --> 00:53:38,970
FIRE BREAKS OUT ON A TRUCK TRANSPORTING
TAEMYUNG CULTURAL FOUNDATION ART

658
00:54:02,073 --> 00:54:03,157
Turn the car around.

659
00:54:05,034 --> 00:54:07,036
[tires screech]

660
00:54:10,331 --> 00:54:12,166
[Dr. Shin] What's this?
She's turning around.

661
00:54:12,750 --> 00:54:13,793
Why? What's going on?

662
00:54:13,876 --> 00:54:15,878
Chair Kim's car is heading back
to the office.

663
00:54:15,962 --> 00:54:17,505
<i>The auctioneer needs to get out fast.</i>

664
00:55:04,260 --> 00:55:06,262
[no audible dialogue]

665
00:55:18,357 --> 00:55:20,901
It's weird. I still can't get the eyes
to look like Mom's.

666
00:55:20,985 --> 00:55:23,487
[inhales sharply]
Well, let me see a second.

667
00:55:24,280 --> 00:55:25,740
[sighs]

668
00:55:25,823 --> 00:55:30,453
It's not that they don't look like hers.
Your mother's eyes are complicated.

669
00:55:31,287 --> 00:55:32,747
Look at them closely.

670
00:55:33,330 --> 00:55:36,625
They hold a story of everything
she's been through her whole entire life.

671
00:55:37,835 --> 00:55:40,838
But what does that mean?

672
00:55:40,921 --> 00:55:42,506
Daddy's complimenting you.

673
00:55:42,590 --> 00:55:46,010
My daughter's finally trying
to see the person, not just the drawing.

674
00:55:46,093 --> 00:55:48,137
I want to draw as good as you, Dad.

675
00:55:48,721 --> 00:55:50,973
Skill improves quickly once you learn.

676
00:55:51,057 --> 00:55:55,728
But, hmm, putting your heart into it…
Not everyone can do that.

677
00:55:55,811 --> 00:56:00,441
My dear Seol-ah has that passion in her.
That's what makes Daddy very proud.

678
00:56:00,524 --> 00:56:02,651
- Really?
- Of course, who's your dad?

679
00:56:02,735 --> 00:56:05,571
Oh, my goodness,
you really are two peas in a pod.

680
00:56:05,654 --> 00:56:08,741
[sighs] Looks like we're going to have
another painter in the family.

681
00:56:08,824 --> 00:56:10,177
And what's wrong with that? [Chuckles]

682
00:56:10,201 --> 00:56:12,703
[clicks tongue]
Seol-ah, don't become a painter.

683
00:56:12,787 --> 00:56:14,371
Be a doctor. A doctor.

684
00:56:14,455 --> 00:56:17,083
Our dear Seol-ah will become
a very famous artist.

685
00:56:17,166 --> 00:56:18,584
- Right?
- Mm-hmm.

686
00:56:18,667 --> 00:56:20,044
[chuckling]

687
00:56:20,127 --> 00:56:22,129
[chuckles]

688
00:56:25,091 --> 00:56:27,593
[Chair Kim] <i>If this ends up</i>
<i>being a posthumous work,</i>

689
00:56:27,676 --> 00:56:33,182
- I'll make sure it sells for a high price.
- [sobs] No! Please, I'm begging you.

690
00:56:33,682 --> 00:56:35,267
[wails]

691
00:56:36,894 --> 00:56:37,895
No!

692
00:56:37,978 --> 00:56:42,691
- Just let me keep it! No! Please!
- [cries]

693
00:56:45,611 --> 00:56:48,030
[coughing, groans]

694
00:57:12,555 --> 00:57:13,764
Whoa, I see her car.

695
00:57:13,848 --> 00:57:15,641
What should we do? Should I crash into it?

696
00:57:15,724 --> 00:57:18,269
<i>She's coming. What do we do? Huh?</i>

697
00:57:18,352 --> 00:57:19,687
I'm going in.

698
00:57:24,859 --> 00:57:27,194
Hurry! She's pulling in!
Come on, seriously!

699
00:57:58,642 --> 00:57:59,643
[device buzzes]

700
00:58:01,770 --> 00:58:02,771
[metal clanks]

701
00:58:11,447 --> 00:58:14,533
- Hmm. You're getting off work late.
- I have a shoot tomorrow.

702
00:58:14,617 --> 00:58:16,410
So I wanted to get ready.

703
00:58:22,917 --> 00:58:24,168
[alarm blaring]

704
00:58:29,048 --> 00:58:30,716
[Seol-ah] <i>The exit code is different.</i>

705
00:58:51,153 --> 00:58:52,363
[blaring continues]

706
00:58:52,446 --> 00:58:53,530
[device buzzes]

707
00:58:56,951 --> 00:58:57,952
[buzzes]

708
00:59:56,427 --> 00:59:58,512
[Chair Kim] <i>First, take care</i>
<i>of that bastard quietly</i>.

709
00:59:58,595 --> 01:00:01,307
It may not be enough,
but the culprit will show up soon.

710
01:00:01,390 --> 01:00:04,852
No. I don't want to use you as bait.

711
01:00:04,935 --> 01:00:07,563
<i>I'm the only one who can get close
without raising any suspicion.</i>

712
01:00:07,646 --> 01:00:09,732
Get her. Don't touch anything.

713
01:00:09,815 --> 01:00:11,066
Han Seol-ah!

714
01:00:11,150 --> 01:00:14,570
[Seol-ah] <i>Until we catch the killer,</i>
<i>nothing is really over.</i>

715
01:00:14,653 --> 01:00:15,946
[Woo-seok] <i>It's been a while.</i>

716
01:00:16,030 --> 01:00:18,407
Your neck will be the one on the line.

717
01:00:18,490 --> 01:00:20,409
- It's all your fault.
- [exclaims]

718
01:00:20,492 --> 01:00:25,789
Well, we'll just have to wait
and see whose neck is on the line.

